LABEL: System
COMMENT: The System class denotes all kind of systems, which may be physical or abstract

LABEL: UnitOfMeasure
COMMENT: A UnitOfMeasure is a standard measure for the ScalarValue of a of PhysicalQuantity.

LABEL: RawMaterial
COMMENT: A RawMaterial is a Material that enters a ProcessStep.

LABEL: isPropertyOf
COMMENT: The relation isPropertyOf links a Property instance to a System instance.

LABEL: ExtensibleValueSet
COMMENT: An ExtensibleValueSet is a ValueEnumeration which, unlike a FixedValueSet, is not defined by an (exhaustive) enumeration of its instances. Thus, the number of possible values may change at run time.

LABEL: hasDimension
COMMENT: The relation hasDimension specifies the PhysicalDimension of a PhysicalQuantity or a UnitOfMeasure.

LABEL: PhysicalDimension
COMMENT: A PhysicalDimension is a characteristic associated with PhysicalQuantities and UnitsOfMeasure for purposes of organization or differentiation. Mass, length, and force are exemplary instances of PhysicalDimension.

LABEL: isValueOf
COMMENT: The relation isValueOf assigns a Value to a Property.

LABEL: hasValue
COMMENT: The hasValue relation designates the Values of a Property.

LABEL: hasOutput
COMMENT: The relation hasOutput connects a Device to an outgoing DirectedConnection.

LABEL: isPredecessorOf
COMMENT: The relation isPredecessorOf identifies all Devices and DirectedConnections that are predecessors of the considered one.

LABEL: QuantitativeValue
COMMENT: A QuantitativeValue is the value of a PhysicalQuantity.

LABEL: IntermediateProduct
COMMENT: An IntermediateProduct is a ChemicalProduct that is produced in a ProcessStep and is used in another ProcessStep in the whole processing system.

LABEL: hasProperty
COMMENT: The relation hasProperty indicates the Properties of a System.

LABEL: ProcessState
COMMENT: A ProcessState represents the collectivity of properties of a CertainMaterialAmount  which is produced in the associating process step.

LABEL: hasUnitOfMeasure
COMMENT: The relation hasUnitOfMeasure establishes the UnitOfMeasure of a ScalarValue.

LABEL: enters
COMMENT: The relation Enters interconnects an ingoing DirectedConnection  to its target Device.

LABEL: Property
COMMENT: The Property class represents the individual properties (traits, qualities) of a System, which distinguish the System from others. Typical examples are Size, Color, or Weight, which are modeled as subclasses of Property.

LABEL: isSuccessorOf
COMMENT: The relation isSuccessorOf identifies all Devices and DirectedConnections that are successors of the considered one.

LABEL: hasInput
COMMENT: The relation hasInput connects a Device to an incoming DirectedConnection.

LABEL: value
COMMENT: The Value attribute holds the actual value of a QualitativeValue.

LABEL: ValueEnumeration
COMMENT: A ValueEnumeration specifies a (finite) set of possible values of a QualitativeValue.

LABEL: leaves
COMMENT: The relation Leaves connects an outgoing DirectedConnection to its source Device.

LABEL: ProcessStep
COMMENT: A ProcessStep is a certain material processing procedure.

LABEL: isConnectedTo
COMMENT: The relation isConnectedTo represents topological connectivity between System.

LABEL: QualitativeValue
COMMENT: A QualitativeValue is a value that is not (numerically) quantifiable.

LABEL: qualitativeValue
COMMENT: The relation qualitativeValue specifies the actual value of a QualitativeValue.

LABEL: Value
COMMENT: The Value class denotes the different values of a Property.

LABEL: isRelatedTo
COMMENT: The relation isRelatedTo subsumes all kinds of inter-system relations.

LABEL: FixedValueSet
COMMENT: A FixedValueSet is a ValueEnumeration that is defined by an exhaustive enumeration of its instances. Thus, the number of possible values is fixed.
